<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 09 at 5:30PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Beaver
County through 600 PM CDT...
At 530 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Knowles, or 10 miles east of Beaver, moving south at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Beaver
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
